{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/timezoneref\/init(identifier:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"init","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"identifier","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"UnsafePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">? = nil)","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"identifier","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" can either be an RFC3339\/ISO 8601 time offset or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"something that would pass as a valid value for the "},{"code":"TZ","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" environment","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"variable (including "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":").","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In Windows, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"identifier"},{"type":"text","text":" can also be the unlocalized name of a time"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"zone for standard time, for example “Pacific Standard Time”."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Valid RFC3339 time offsets are "},{"code":"\"Z\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" (for UTC) or"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"±hh:mm\""},{"type":"text","text":".  ISO 8601 additionally specifies"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"±hhmm\""},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"±hh\""},{"text":".  Offsets are","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"time values to be added to Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) to get"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the local time.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In UNIX, the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TZ"},{"text":" environment variable typically corresponds","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to the name of a file in the zoneinfo database, an absolute path to a file","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"somewhere else, or a string in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"“std offset [dst [offset],start[\/time],end[\/time]]” (POSIX) format.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"There  are  no spaces in the specification. The name of standard"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and daylight savings time zone must be three or more alphabetic"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"characters. Offsets are time values to be added to local time to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"get Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) and should be"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"[±]hh[[:]mm[:ss]]\""},{"text":".  Dates are either","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"\"Jn\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" (Julian day with n between 1 and 365, leap"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"years not counted), ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"n\""},{"text":" (zero-based Julian day","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with n between 0 and 365) or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"Mm.w.d\""},{"text":" (day d","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"(0 <= d <= 6) of week w (1 <= w <= 5) of month m (1 <= m <= 12), day"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"0 is a Sunday).  Times are in local wall clock time, the default is","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"02:00:00.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In Windows, the “tzn[+|–]hh"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"#dzn","type":"reference"},{"text":"” format is used, but also","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"accepts POSIX format.  The Windows format uses US rules for all time","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"zones; daylight savings time is 60 minutes behind the standard time"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with date and time of change taken from Pacific Standard Time."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Offsets are time values to be added to the local time to get","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Coordinated Universal Time (UTC).","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"g_time_zone_new_local()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" calls this function with the value of the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"TZ","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" environment variable. This function itself is independent of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the value of ","type":"text"},{"code":"TZ","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", but if "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"identifier"},{"type":"text","text":" is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":" then ","type":"text"},{"code":"\/etc\/localtime","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will be consulted to discover the correct time zone on UNIX and the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"registry will be consulted or ","type":"text"},{"code":"GetTimeZoneInformation()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will be used"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to get the local time zone on Windows."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If intervals are not available, only time zone rules from "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TZ"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"environment variable or other means, then they will be computed","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from year 1900 to 2037.  If the maximum year for the rules is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"available and it is greater than 2037, then it will followed","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"instead.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"http:\/\/tools.ietf.org\/html\/rfc3339#section-5.6"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for a precise definition of valid RFC3339 time offsets"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(the ","type":"text"},{"code":"time-offset","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" expansion) and ISO 8601 for the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"full list of valid time offsets.  See"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"http:\/\/www.gnu.org\/s\/libc\/manual\/html_node\/TZ-Variable.html","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"for an explanation of the possible","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"values of the "},{"code":"TZ","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" environment variable. See","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"http:\/\/msdn.microsoft.com\/en-us\/library\/ms912391%28v=winembedded.11%29.aspx","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"for the list of time zones on Windows.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You should release the return value by calling "},{"code":"g_time_zone_unref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"when you are done with it.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneRef"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneRef\/init(identifier:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"role":"symbol","title":"init(identifier:)","symbolKind":"init","roleHeading":"Initializer","fragments":[{"text":"init","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"identifier","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar"},{"text":">?)","kind":"text"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib11TimeZoneRefV10identifierACSPys4Int8VGSg_tcfc","extendedModule":"GLib"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"text":"Creates a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZone"},{"type":"text","text":" corresponding to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"identifier"},{"type":"text","text":". If "},{"code":"identifier","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" cannot be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"parsed or loaded, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":" is returned.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/TimeZoneRef/init(identifier:)":{"fragments":[{"text":"init","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"identifier","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"UnsafePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar"},{"text":">?)","kind":"text"}],"title":"init(identifier:)","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/timezoneref\/init(identifier:)","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneRef\/init(identifier:)","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Creates a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZone","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" corresponding to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"identifier"},{"type":"text","text":". If "},{"code":"identifier","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" cannot be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"parsed or loaded, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":" is returned.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol"},"http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3339#section-5.6":{"titleInlineContent":[{"text":"RFC3339 §5.6","type":"text"}],"title":"RFC3339 §5.6","identifier":"http:\/\/tools.ietf.org\/html\/rfc3339#section-5.6","type":"link","url":"http:\/\/tools.ietf.org\/html\/rfc3339#section-5.6"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/TimeZone":{"role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"TimeZone"}],"kind":"symbol","title":"TimeZone","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"TimeZone"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/timezone","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTimeZone"},{"text":" represents a time zone, at no particular point in time.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZone"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/TimeZoneRef":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneRef","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"TimeZoneRef"}],"type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"code":"GTimeZone","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" represents a time zone, at no particular point in time.","type":"text"}],"title":"TimeZoneRef","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"TimeZoneRef"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/timezoneref"},"#dzn":{"titleInlineContent":[{"text":":mm[:ss]","type":"text"}],"identifier":"#dzn","title":":mm[:ss]","type":"link","url":"#dzn"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","title":"GLib","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib","abstract":[]},"http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms912391%28v=winembedded.